post_text:
2020 Homecoming Parade Information

The 2020 homecoming parade will take place on Friday, September 18th. The parade will begin at 1:30 PM, and the line up will start at 1:00 PM. The homecoming theme this year is "Surf the Turf to Victory." We hope to have an abundance of parade entries from businesses and other entities.

If you would like to enter a float for the 2020 homecoming parade, please, contact Tess Rinehart, Student Council Sponsor, at tess.rinehart@mtayrschools.org OR (641)-464-0512. Entries need to be in by Friday, September 11th.

*See the picture for the parade route below, which is the same as last year.

post_text:
Download the FanFood App to order concessions at our home events & some away games will also have this available at their concessions. *You will still have the option of ordering at the window and paying cash.
The FanFood App can be found in the app store for iPhones & Androids. Once downloaded it will walk you through what to do and any concession stands close to you will show up. With this option you pay with your credit card and do not have to have cash with you. If you are having problems finding the app be sure you scan the QR code that will be on our programs.

post_text:
MS/HS Bulletin

SWCC Classes & Textbooks If you did not pick up your college textbooks on Monday, please pick these up in the school counseling office. College Algebra begins: Wednesday, August 19th, at 7 AM in the auditorium Online classes begin: Monday, August 24th

Attention Sophomores, Juniors, and Seniors There will be an ACT test date on September 12th at Graceland College in Lamoni, IA. We suggest if you are thinking about taking the ACT this year that you sign up for it.

9th - 12th Grade If you are interested in running for Class Officer or Student Council representative. Please, check your email from Mrs. Rinehart to print out the nomination form. Turn it into the school counselor's office by Friday at 3:30 if you would like to run for office. Voting will occur on Monday.

High School Scheduling You have three days to change your schedule. Thursday, August 20th, at 3:30, is your last day to add drop your classes. These changes MUST BE APPROVED by the teacher. You will need to have them sign a green slip or send Mrs. Rinehart an email approving your schedule changes.

post_text: Mount Ayr Elementary "Meet the Teacher Night" will be held on Monday, August 17th, from 5:30-7:00. Students can visit their classrooms at anytime between 5:30 and 7:00. Reminder - we're trying to limit the amount of adults in the building. We'd like 3rd, 4th, 5th, and 6th grade students to attend without parents (unless new to the district). We'd like only one parent to attend with 1st and 2nd grade students. All parents can attend with Kindergarten students at their scheduled meeting times. Please wear a mask to "Meet the Teacher Night." We look forward to seeing our students!

post_text: Safety is our number one priority at MACS. Due to the Covid-19 pandemic we have had to adjust many plans for opening school this year. The CDC and IDPH have recommended masks be worn when school resumes with face to face instruction. We are asking parents to acquire washable cloth masks for their students as we will be following this recommendation as part of our Return to Learn Plan. Five/5 Cloth masks would be ideal, one for each day and then washing them to re-use the following week. We wanted to make this adjustment right away so you could address this with your school supplies and perhaps find some 'trendy' styles before they are all gone. We will have extra masks at school, should your student need one. Those students or staff with medical exemptions will not be required to wear masks. We will be starting school face to face while exercising physical distancing within the buildings. We will have more guidance coming out on specific pieces of our plan soon... Thank you. ------- Mount Ayr Community Schools

Mt. Ayr Community School in compliance with CDC and IDPH recommendations will be hosting an outdoor graduation ceremony.

Date and Time: Sunday at 1:00 P.M., July 19, 2020
Location: Raider Football Field
Seniors will need to arrive at 12:00 P.M. for pictures and instructions.
The gates will open at 12:30 for spectators.
We encourage all spectators to practice social distancing. The home and visitor bleachers will be available for seating. The graduates will be socially distanced on the football field/track facing the home bleachers for the ceremony.
This event will be held outdoors please dress accordingly for the weather.
Umbrellas will be allowed and spectators can bring in drinks. No food will be allowed.
To accommodate everyone who might have COVID-19 or weather concerns the event will be live-streamed at https://www.citylinktv.com/channel/mount-ayr-community-schools/

A few things to note:

1. Games are assumed to be JV-Varsity unless noted. A few schools are still assessing their numbers, so that could change.

2. The Pride of Iowa conference has implemented a "no delay" policy for this year. If the game is stopped for lightning, rain, etc, it will be over at that point.

3. In conjunction with the no-delay policy, conference schools will take a very cautious & proactive approach to weather-related decisions. So if the forecast at noon includes a good chance of rain at 6:00, the game will likely be canceled.

4. It is highly unlikely that any canceled games will be rescheduled.

June 3 at 6:05 PM ¬∑

A few things to note:
1. Games are assumed to be JV-Varsity unless noted. A few schools are still assessing their numbers, so that could change.
2. The Pride of Iowa conference has implemented a "no delay" policy for this year. If the game is stopped for lightning, rain, etc, it will be over at that point.
3. In conjunction with the no-delay policy, conference schools will take a very cautious & proactive approach to weather-related decisions. So if the forecast at noon includes a good chance of rain at 6:00, the game will likely be canceled.
4. It is highly unlikely that any canceled games will be rescheduled.

8th-, 9th-, 10th-, and 11th-grade students,

A lot of important information was sent to you via email by Mrs. Rinehart this morning. She sent you emails regarding scheduling for the 2020-2021 academic school year as well as SWCC enrollment paperwork. She is requesting that you complete the scheduling Google Form and SWCC enrollment paperwork by Monday, May 18th.

If you have any questions, please email her at tess.rinehart@mtayrschools.org. She has scheduled Google Meet meetings for each grade at different times on Friday, May 15th, to discuss scheduling questions and concerns. Those times are provided in the email. If you would like to schedule individual online meeting times, please contact Mrs. Rinehart, and she will schedule those with you.

Again, please complete this process by Monday, May 18th. Your chosen schedule is not guaranteed as there are many factors contributing to the scheduling process. If you do not complete the scheduling Google Form provided in your email, Mrs. Rinehart will schedule for you. Thanks. Have a great week!

We've had some questions about athletic physicals for 7th-12th grade. This is really all we know right now:

Guidance Requested from Department of Education
We are awaiting additional guidance from DE to finalize guidance regarding:

Pre-Participation Physicals

Coach-Athlete Out-of-season contact

As soon as the Governor signs off on the changes, we will share the details with you.

So basically we aren't sure how athletic physicals will work this year. But don't wait until the last minute to schedule your athletic physical just in case it takes a while to get an appointment at your chosen doctor's office or just in case the Department of Education doesn't get the OK to extend the use of last year's physicals.
Appointments can be made at both clinics in town. Here is the physical form if you would like to go ahead and schedule your physical. https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gTeHSIMMjoE6rX64a7282KMijcfp7sDM/view?usp=sharing

text:
We've had some questions about athletic physicals for 7th-12th grade. This is really all we know right now:

Guidance Requested from Department of Education
We are awaiting additional guidance from DE to finalize guidance regarding:

Pre-Participation Physicals

Coach-Athlete Out-of-season contact

As soon as the Governor signs off on the changes, we will share the details with you.

So basically we aren't sure how athletic physicals will work this year. But don't wait until the last minute to schedule your athletic physical just in case it takes a while to get an appointment at your chosen doctor's office or just in case the Department of Education doesn't get the OK to extend the use of last year's physicals.
Appointments can be made at both clinics in town. Here is the physical form if you would like to go ahead and schedule your physical. https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gTeHSIMMjoE6rX64a7282KMijcfp7sDM/view?usp=sharing

post_text:
Hey, Class of 2020!

Did you know that May 1st is National Decision Day?
Do you know what National Decision Day is?

National Decision Day is a day for us to celebrate you, high school seniors, and the decisions that you are making after high school. Some of you are choosing to attend college, some are choosing apprenticeships, some are choosing trade schools, and others are joining the workforce, and we are so proud of you!

To celebrate you, we will be handing out doughnuts to Mt. Ayr Schools' graduating senior students on Decision Day, Friday, May 1st in the east (student) parking lot from 8 AM to 9 AM.

Wear your future college and decision gear to pick up your doughnut. Thanks to Ms. Klommhaus, Mrs. Neas, and TRIO for making this opportunity available to our students!

Also, to stay safe, please stay in your car, and we will deliver the doughnut to your window. Those delivering doughnuts will be wearing masks and gloves to keep you safe as well.

We hope to see you Friday and congrats on your post-secondary decisions and commitments!
